One man, who had become trapped inside a seventh story flat and is yet to be named, was pronounced dead at the scene.

There were not thought to be any other fatalities or injuries. 

The fire is now under control. 

A spokesman for Avon Fire and Rescue service confirmed the death.

He said: 'At this stage we have no idea what the cause of the ignition was.

'We have two fire investigators on the scene who are are liaising with police investigators.

'One man was unfortunately declared dead. Surprisingly, for such a large fire, no other people were injured.' 

An Avon and Somerset Police spokesman said: 'It's a fairly intense fire so it is being dealt with by fire officers primarily. Police are on the scene.'

He added that it was too early to know whether the fire was suspicious. 

